snippet.textDisplay:
Okay I hopefully figure it out.


So many of Joji's songs are about the death of a relationship. He got into a relationship where he was constantly insecure about himself and the feelings of the girl he's with. He didn't feel like she actually wanted him (Slow Dancing In The Dark) "You should be with him, I can't compete". As he got closer to her, she realized his depression was worse than she thought and started backing away because of her realization of who he really is. (demons) "This is not a threat, I promise. It's a warning, baby, I just want you to know", he is warning her about the demons but even that isn't enough to prepare her for his real sadness. She promised him she'd help him with them but after realizing just how depressed he is she ran away, (Run) "I witnessed your madness, you shed light on my sins . And if we share in this sadness, then where have you been?"


She realized she didn't want to be with him forever (Run) "I know you're not in love, like you used to be . 'Cause I'm not the one, like you used to think" and had only wanted to be with him for a small period of time (Test Drive) "I'm looking for a long ride, she just wants a test drive" . So she leaves him, and he gets heartbroken. He gets attached, and is unable to move on (can't get over you) "I can't get over you". He starts going through the stages of grief:


1. Denial: (Run) "Guess I'm not enough, like you used to think . So I'll just run" He starts to run away from his feelings to cope with the breakup. (I'll see you in 40) "I was hiding too, It's alright."



2. Anger: (Yeah Right) "Yeah, you bet I know that she ain't never give a single fuck about me" He gets angry about her and starts hating her for breaking his heart. (Bitter Fuck) "You made me sad and you made me mean . And now I'm mad, I feel unclean". He also gets jealous by the fact that she's with someone else (can't get over you) "If I can't have you, no one can".


3. Bargaining: (I'll see you in 40) "If you were 22 forever, would be nice" He is trying to convince himself that if the relationship stayed like it was when they were younger and happy, then she wouldn't have left him. He doesn't want to acknowledge that his depression was the cause of the breakup.


4. Oh boy, Depression: (will he) "And now I'm sad, I'm a mess" He has fallen deeper into the depression and can't take it anymore, "I need you, back . I need you back. Where'd you go? I thought we'd last forever" He feels lost now that she's gone. He can't cope being without her since he had felt dependent on her, the reason that she left in the first place. He wants to find her because he feels lost without her (run) "And I travel the country just to get to you"


5. Acceptance: (will he): "Will he treat you like shit just the way that I did? 'Cause I don't blame you" Joji comes to the realization that the break up was partly his fault too, and gets over it. (I'll see you in 40) "I won't come around , I will find myself, And I still love you" in the final lines of that song he accepts the breakup and decides to instead find himself rather than her.


wow that was long, thanks for reading my theory.
